---
// Peninsula Insider — Phase 1 Astro scaffold placeholder
//
// This page exists so the scaffold is a real, runnable Astro project.
// It is intentionally minimal. The full homepage rebuild happens in
// Week 1–3 per roadmap-2026-04-09.md § 4.7.
//
// The eventual homepage will be driven by `homepage.json` and composed
// from editorial modules:
//   1. Cover story
//   2. This Weekend
//   3. Five pillars
//   4. Map strip
//   5. Authority list
//   6. Journal
//   7. Newsletter
//
// Do not build out the full chrome here yet. This file is the seed.
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Peninsula Insider — Astro rebuild scaffold</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Phase 1 Astro scaffold for Peninsula Insider. Content collections, JSON-first authoring, editorial homepage rebuild pending."
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #f7f3ec;
        --ink: #1b1b18;
        --muted: #6d685f;
        --rule: #d6cec1;
        --accent: #9c3f2d;
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      main {
        max-width: 860px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 72px 24px 96px;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0 0 16px;
        font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 8vw, 4.8rem);
        line-height: 0.98;
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      .dek {
        max-width: 52rem;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
        gap: 16px;
        margin: 40px 0;
      }

      .card {
        padding: 18px;
        border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      }

      .card h2 {
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        font-size: 1.05rem;
      }

      .card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.96rem;
      }

      hr {
        border: 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
        margin: 40px 0;
      }

      ul {
        padding-left: 1.2rem;
      }

      code {
        font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
        font-size: 0.95em;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <span class="eyebrow">Phase 1 scaffold</span>
      <h1>Peninsula Insider is moving to Astro.</h1>
      <p class="dek">
        This is the migration seed, not the finished homepage. The live site is
        still the legacy flat HTML build while the new content layer, atomic page
        model, and editorial homepage are assembled in parallel.
      </p>

      <div class="grid">
        <section class="card">
          <h2>What exists already</h2>
          <p>Typed content collections, JSON-first data directories, TypeScript config, and a credible project skeleton.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="card">
          <h2>What comes next</h2>
          <p>Venue templates, place hubs, Journal collection wiring, and the homepage module system described in the roadmap.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="card">
          <h2>Why this matters</h2>
          <p>The old site is brochureware. The new site becomes an editorial publication with atomic URLs and AI-authorable structured content.</p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>Immediate next implementation steps</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create one seed venue record and render it through an Astro route.</li>
        <li>Create six seed place files for Red Hill, Merricks, Sorrento, Flinders, Dromana, and Cape Schanck.</li>
        <li>Add <code>homepage.json</code> and scaffold the seven homepage modules.</li>
        <li>Stand up the first Journal article in the <code>articles</code> collection.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        See <code>../README.md</code> in this project root and
        <code>../../docs/roadmap-2026-04-09.md</code> for the working plan.
      </p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
